chapters.chName: Your Father, the Number One Hero

chapters.oneLineSummary: Hawks continues to clean up Hood's fissions, then assists Endeavor by giving him his wings.

pages.summary: Hawks has cut down two fissions. 'Hrm... Not so tough.' His other heroes exclaim about how they need to work on hunting more fissions. Hawks looks to a building exploding in the distance

Hawks slashes at Hood and hits it with feathers that don't seem to bother it. 'Endeavor! My feathers Don't pack enough punch. But they make up for it with speed. I was watching you this whole time. I get it.' he thinks.

Hawks, thinking: 'THere was nobody else out there really trying to surpass him [All Might]. Only you! You were the one working to surpass him!' An image of small and adult Hawks look at Endeavor facing the canyon that separates him from All Might. 'Nah, never gonna happen. How Awkward can one by be? I mean, c'mon.' Now, Hawks things 'My feathers are already flying your way.'
Hawks' feathers give Endeavor wings. Hawks thinks,' My speed added to your fire-power! I'll push you forward, no. 1!'

chapters.oneLineSummary: Hawks watches Endeavor defeat Hood, helps him afterward, and spots Dabi.

pages.summary: Hawks thinks: 'I wanted to be stronger than anyone, seeing my back's not all that reassuring'. His visor breaks.
Hawks says 'For real?'
Hawks lands on a roof and thinks 'Still not enough firepower?! My feathers! I shot all of 'em and they're nearly burned up.' Endeavor calls his name.
Hawks watches Endeavor try to burn Hood from the inside.
From the roof, Hawks says 'I can't help you much, since they're burnt to a crisp.'
'I get it. Up there he doesn't have to hold back.
Hawks watches Endeavor Prominance Burn Hood.
Hawks runs towards Endeavor

Hawks holds Endeavor up. 'That's All Might's pose, you know?' Endeavor says AM uses his left. Hawks helps Endeavor sit. 'Who cares about that? I'm just greatful you won.' Endeavor isn't pleased by his performance. 'If I may disagree this victory of yours, today was absolutely huge. First, let's do something about your wounds.
Hawks looks up as Dabi appears.

chapters.oneLineSummary: Hawks argues with Dabi about his loyalty to the LOV, then remembers being told to infiltrate them.

pages.summary: Hawks talks to Endeavor. 'Take it easy. I'll handle him. I only have my tiny feathers left, but I can at least buy us some time.
Hawks glares at Dabi and dodges his flame.
Hawks is surprised by Miruko.
Hawks scowls as Dabi begins to vomit goo.
A primary feather zooms into Hawks' hand as Dabi disappears. Hawks glances around. 'Anyway..'
'Seems the day is saved.' Hawks holds on to Endeavor.

Hawks holds his primary at Dabi's throat. 'How about some actual cooperation, Dabi?' When dabi says he thought Hawks had only baby feathers left, he answers, 'You think I'd meet with a liar like you unarmed?'

Hawks speaks with Dabi. 'It was supposed to be tomorrow. And not downtown, but at the factory by the water. Plus, this nomy was clearly a cut above the rest. You could've mentioned that beforehand.' Dabi says he changed his mind and says Hawks is guilty of not communicating honestly himself, and bringing Endeavor instead of a weaker hero. 'I thought you'd be thrilled to inflict that kind of damage on him. Besides, you're the one who broke our agreement.'

Dabi wonders if Hawks really sympathises with the villains. 'I gotta keep up appearances. A hero can't go go losing the public's trust. The more faith they have in me, the juicier the intel I can get. That's to your advantage. Try taking the long view, here. What I do, I do for The League's sake, Dabi.' He leaves Dabi.

Hawks remembers a conversation with the HPSC. 'Join the League of Villains, Hawks.' 'Huh? Hang on, what am I missing here? There's that search team already, right? With Gran Torino and them?' a HPSC worker answers, 'How did you know? that's never been disclosed.'

The HPSC people explain they need Hawks to be a spy. 'What about people they hurt while I'm infiltrating? Do I just turn a blind eye to that?' He's told he will turn a blind eye. Hawks visits Endeavor in the hospital.
Hawks meets Endeavor.

Hawks and Endeavor are walking. 'I'm Just glad you didn't lose your left eye. Especially since it wouldn've been my fault.' Endeavor says it is his responsibility, and remarks on the coincidence of the nomu going for them the moment they arrived in town. 'sure is,' Hawks says, and thinks 'You're killing me here, man.' he continues out loud: 'But of course the new top two are gonna attract attention, walking around near the station. The enemy must've spotted us and jumped on the opportunity. Internally, he thinks 'Telling him to get out there and drum up supprt was just an excuse to position him for an attack that was meant to come the next day.'

Hawks thinks, 'The fact that I'm in contact with teh villains has gotta stay top secret.' outloud he says 'It's also possible that the rumor about nomu popping up were just bait to lure heroes out to hunt. Anyhow, I'd better get in touch with the team searching for the league.' Endeavor tells him to watch his back and says they'll need to cooperate. Hawks is excited. 'Didn't know you cared, Endeavor!' he says. 'Once my plumage has grown back, I'll be airborne and active again. It'll probably just take another day or so. You'll take it easy too, I hope? See you later!'

Hawks remembers talking with the HPSC's President. 'Is all this really necessary?' HPSC says that's why they suggested it. 'Suggest it? Funny calling it a suggestion when it's an offer I can't refuse. Shame on you.' The president says they're glad he couldn't make it to Kamino. Hawks remembers a traffic accident where he saved people.

Hawks remembers being approached by HPSC agents as a homeless child. To the HPSC President, he says, 'If dirtying my hands can somehow bring everyon epeace of mind... I'll gladly take on this task.' 'I'm Hawks' The think in the present. 'The man who's a bit too fast. A soceity where heroes can enjoy a little boredom... I'll make it happen, I promise, at my trademark top speed.

Hawks stands atop a poll with a villain captured by feathers. 'Too slow.' He always finished the job on his own. Apparently, this was the first year he scouted someone from the sports festival. 'ext stop is The Cantina bar, where they've got a customer going wild! You guys handle the rest here.' The sidekicks, including Tokoyami, are left behind. 'Can't stay around yapping while the next crisis is getting worse.'

Tokoyami wonders why hawks chose him. 'Cuz we're birds of a feather,' Hawks answers, holding up a feather. Tokoyami asks if he's serious. 'I'm 20 percent serious. And half of me just wanted to chat with a kid from Class 1-A About those punks who attacked you guys--The League of Villains. And wouldn't you know it? there you were, killed, sharp-looking cream of hte crop... a fellow bird who could probably keep up with me.'
Hawks is flying to his next incident when Tokoyami races after him. Hawks looks behind himself: 'heh'.

Hawks and Tokoyami talk. 'Good Work today. Hey, tokoyami... psst. How about a nice night flight?' Hawks picks up Tokoyami and carries him over the city. Tokoyami yells excitedly. 'First time flying I take it. 'That final 30 percent? I saw you in action, Tokoyami, and thought 'what a waste!' Being up in the sy in a great thing. You get a bird's eye view of the world.'

'Not that 'm much for training the next generation or whatever.' Tokoyami wants to know what's a waste. 'Focusing on close combat. It's fine to cover for your weaknesses, but don't forget to improve on your real talents.' they land atop a tower. 'Let yourself move freely. Listen, from one bird to another... those who can fly, should!'
Hawks looks at Tokoyami. 'Why keep yourself grounded?
Tokoyami says, 'As Hawks would say, speed beats power.
Tokoyami says he and shoto are responsible for upholding Hawks and Endeavors' reputations.

chapters.chName: The New Power and All For One
chapters.oneLineSummary: Komori asks for pictures of Hawks

pages.summary: Komori asks Tokoyami if he has any pictures of Hawks.
Redestro threatens reveal the League of Villain's location to the heroes (including Hawks)

chapters.oneLineSummary: Hawks attends the Paranormal Liberation Front gathering.

pages.summary: Hawks claps along at the announcement of the PLF. 'I'm too late!' he thinks. this explains why he let me in so easily... If only someone had taken down The League sooner, all those good little citizens wouldn't have had to die...' he remembers presenting Dabi with a bag and saying 'What really happened over in Deika? That was you guys, right?'

Best Jeanist was inside the bag Hawks' remembered. Hawks keeps thinking. 'An army's worth of soldiers, united under a single commanding will. Feel Good Inc. With total control of the network. Detnerat, with its deep ties to industry, and probably at least a few more of those high-end nomu. You could do whatever you want... Even in this superpowered society overflowing with heroes. You, Shigaraki have amassed power on par with those very heroes. Maybe even greater.

Dabi slings an arm over Hawks' and says he's looking pleased. 'Sure am!' says Hawks. Now how about some intros?' 'Can't make a move yet,' he thinks. There's still their backer in the shadows. I gotta figure out thewhole story here ASAP before calling in Endeavor and the others. C'mon, Hawks! If you're not quick enough.... All of Japan is done for.'
Hawks returns to the PLF mansion. 'I'm Baaack!' Slidin' Go asks where he's been. 'Just getting some proper coffee. That black sludge you got here is not for me.

Slidin' Go chastises Hawks for going out without permission. Hawks: 'Huh? isn't the liberation army all about giving people freedom?' Slidin' Go answers that he's ranked higher. 'YEssir!' Hawks Salutes. Skeptic appears to rebuke Slidin' Go. Hawks' wings are covered in audio and visual sky equipment to track his movements and interactions.
Hawks drinks his coffee. Skeptic says they stocked up on black coffe. 'What can I say? Some like it sweet,' says Hawks.

Hawks remembers reporting to the HPSC while flying with the large bag. 'I finally made contact with Dabi. He's still wary of me and my correspondence with you guys is going to be monitored. From this point on, all communication needs to be in code. For now, figuring out where the nomy come from is top priority. Over and out.'
A villain appears, and Hawks looks down from a high building. 'Aw man, what horrible timing...' Hawks is holding a copy of a book called Meta Liberation War.
Hawks' feathers appear as Endeavor and his interns battle Starservant
Hawks enters the battle, capturing three criminals with his feathers. 'Oh! Trainees! My bad. Looks like I was a little faster.'
The three criminals fall to the ground. 'Seemed like you were in trouble, Endeavor,' Hawks says. Endeavor denies it. Hawks says 'But it seemed that way, didn't it Shoto?'
Endeavor complains that Hawks should tell him when he's in town. Hawks answers 'I'm not, I mean, I was just passing by.' His wing clearly shows a bug.
Izuku greets Hawks as the villains are led away by police. 'You're the kid who smashes up his own fingers, right?

'Tsukuyomi filled me in. Man I wish I could've worked with that kid again.' Izuku says that Tokoyami is at his agency. Hawks rubs his neck. 'Yeah, down in my hometown with my sidekicks. But i've got too much going on to be there. I feel kinda bad about it.' Endeavor asks what Hawks wants.

'Want, oh nothing really,' Hawks pulls the Meta Liberation War book from his pocket. 'But have you read this book, Endeavor? I mean, you must've heard of it. This thing's been flying off the shelves lately. And after those townspeople in Deika fought for their lives, the book's been getting even more attention.' Hawks says. Internally, he thinks 'sorry I have to beat around the bush so much.' out loud, he continues: 'It was written way back when, but it feels really relevant today. Like this quote-- 'When freedom is only granted to a selevt few, the burden neccessarily shifts to everyone else.' If you don't got time for heavy reading, I highlighted the must-read parts! It outlines Destro's ultimate ideal: a society held together by personal responsibility! it's perfect for this day and age!' Internally, Hawks thinks 'This is the only way I can get the message across right now.'

Hawks stares at endeavor, thinking 'please pick up on what I'm saying number one hero!' out loud, he says 'imagine it, Endeavor... a world where we've got time to kill!' Hawks remembers when, at their meal before the nomu, Hawks said 'I wanna make this world one where heroes have time to kill.'
